# SETREP — keep production settlement config OUT of the repo.
# Only the password-encrypted explorer should ever be committed.

# Encrypted explorer is the ONLY allowed deliverable (force-tracked below)
# Plaintext / sensitive outputs — never commit:
SETREP_dependency_explorer.html
SETREP_dependency_lineage.xlsx
SETREP_dependency_report.docx
setrep_config.db
*.db

# Raw Oracle exports / dumps
*.sql
*.pde
*.dmp
*.csv

# Intermediate build artifacts
bundle.json
graph.json
*.log

# Local / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.tmp

# Explicitly allow the encrypted file even if a rule above would catch it
!SETREP_dependency_explorer_LOCKED.html
